    "For instance, a tester may be unable to reliably determine whether a test case failed a program or was due to noise in quantum computations.",
    "To this end, a set of approaches were recently proposed [113][114][115][116].",
    "Muqeet et al.",
    "[115,116] proposed two machine learning-based approaches to learn noise patterns as machine learning models for a given quantum computer or noisy simulator.",
    "Such machine learning models are then used to filter out noise from the outputs of quantum programs, thereby improving testing reliability."
